config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_RNG_TYPER
    bool "RNG Typer behavior (dice rolls, random ints, random strings)"
    depends on ENTROPY_GENERATOR
    help
      Enables a ZMK behavior that uses the nRF52 hardware RNG to type:
        - Dice rolls in dXX: N format
        - Full raw 32-bit random integers
        - Random 16-character strings with selectable charset

      Key timing follows CONFIG_ZMK_MACRO_DEFAULT_TAP_MS and
      CONFIG_ZMK_MACRO_DEFAULT_WAIT_MS (both default 30ms).

      IMPORTANT: The default behavior queue size (CONFIG_ZMK_BEHAVIORS_QUEUE_SIZE=64)
      is too small for 16-char strings. Add to your .conf:
        CONFIG_ZMK_BEHAVIORS_QUEUE_SIZE=128
